title: Can't open open local webpage in Firefox (MacOS)
content:
I have a local webpage on my home network (Raspberry Pi) that I load all the time on my mac laptop using Safari and/or Firefox.

When opening this local webpage earlier this week in Firefox, some message came up which I didn't read and blindly clicked OK. Now the local page will not load ("We can’t connect to the server at webpage.local.").

I does still load in safari. And it does load using FireFox on my iphone (I use SYNC). So I somehow messed up my desktop firefox.

Searched online and have tried all sorts of things with no success (refresh Firefox, re-install, clear cache, etc).

Any suggestions on fixing this would be appreciated.

Jim Firefox 130.01 (MacOS 15.0)

title: can't select items in menus
content:
Hi - have been having an issue since 128 where I can't select items in certain menus in Firefox with the mouse. Each time I open Firefox, it works once. Subsequently, the focus in the menu is completely off from where I put my mouse, and I can't click anything. (I would upload a video, but there doesn't seem to be a way). An example of the behavior is: -hamburger menu open. Mouse is on 'Translate page', but focus is on 'save page as'.

  • This happens with both the trackpad and the mouse.
  • I don't experience this issue with other applications.
  • I can navigate some of the menu options with the keyboard. For example, in the Bookmark menu I can select Save, but not Remove bookmark.
  • I don't have any issue with the main nav bar (File, Edit, etc)

This applies to for example: Save bookmarks (cmd+d), Hamburger Menu, and the new Translation dialog (where it prompts you to translate). I can't inspect them to see if they are all the same component that is causing the issue, because they disappear if you choose Inspect. (I'm unable to see a "Disable popup autohide" setting in my meatball menu, as described here). I also tried the steps listed [https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/que.../957538] here. Things I have tried:

  • resetting PRAM/SMC just in case
  • disabling hardware acceleration
  • starting in safe mode
  • refreshing Firefox
  • updating to the latest version (twice)

machine: MacBook Pro Retina, 13-inch, Mid 2014

title: Disabling data mining options break Card Preview and sites with Let's Encrypt certificates
content:
Disabling either the "Allow Firefox to send technical and interaction data to Mozilla" or the "Allow Firefox to install and run studies" options under the Privacy & Security settings page break all of my homelab SSL certificates using Let's Encrypt and breaks the tab/card preview functionality. The only way for these to work is to leave both options enabled. Disabling either one breaks both of those.

When they are disabled the card preview just doesn't work. The Let's Encrypt-backed self-hosted services are a bit different. I get a warning that the pages are insecure, and if I click the Advanced button to continue (sometimes it is there and sometimes it is not) I get looped back to the same insecure page with no way to accept or proceed.

Things I've tried: - Disabled all Add-Ons - Deleted/reverted all modified settings in about:config - Firefox Refresh - Uninstalled/cleared cache directories/reinstalled - Deleted my whole Mozilla account and recreated, thinking it was a bad setting being synced

Fedora Systems information: - Firefox v130.0.1, Mozilla Firefox Flatpak - Flathub Flatpak from official Mozilla source - OS: Fedora 40, Gnome - Hardware: Framework 13 12th-gen laptop, custom desktop PC

Ubuntu System information: - Firefox v130.0.1, Mozilla Firefox Snap for Ubuntu - Snap as provided from fresh Ubuntu installation - OS: Ubuntu 22.04.4, Gnome - Hardware: Lenovo ThinkPad X13 Gen4, Intel 13th-gen

This is not an issue on Firefox for Android seemingly. This started on my laptop first a few weeks ago, I don't remember changing either of those privacy settings at the time but I may have.

title: My Website Not Reloading in Firefox
content:
Hi there,

I'm experiencing an issue where my website, "https://oceanofpdf.co.uk/", is not reloading properly in Firefox. When I try to refresh the page, it either hangs or doesn't display the updated content. This problem seems specific to Firefox, as the website works fine on other browsers like Chrome and Edge.

I've cleared my cache, tried private browsing mode, and even disabled all add-ons, but the problem persists. Could anyone help me figure out what might be causing this issue and how to resolve it? Any insights or troubleshooting steps would be greatly appreciated.

Thanks in advance!
